<br>
After this Thursday Patch, I noticed that that restriction seems to have been removed.<br>
<br>
I was playing around with a new warrior trying to get defense up, and he was getting hit by about 8 fire beetles at the same time. I had a new cleric heal him, and the mobs all kept attacking the warrior. After the warrior died, the bugs *all* rushed and whacked the cleric.<br>
<br>
Anyhow, anyone notice when this phenomenon started happening?<br>
<br>
It makes defense practice under L10 nice and easy.<br>
<br>
It might also make raiding somewhat different as well, as the behaviour changes on a multi-mob pull. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usmallcutepuppy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>smallcutepuppy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 519<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/27/02 11:11:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2808.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: # of MELEE mobs that attack you at 1 time (patch?)</span><hr size=1> It would make pets useful on raids if they could all attack at once. With all these beastlord tweaks I ought to reroll as one. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uthraallfv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ThraallFV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 169<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/27/02 11:25:09 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2808.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: # of MELEE mobs that attack you at 1 time (patch?)</span><hr size=1> The pet thing has been fixed long ago.  the only time pets had a problem of to many other pets attack is when its a charmed/direcharmed pet.<br>
